        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>This is a polarization project, using the default set-up.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_CORRELATOR</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>The primary goal is to resolve the magnetic field structure on the 0.05 pc (corresponding to 2" for a source distance of 5.32 kpc) scale, so we request an angular resolution of 0.5". To effectively recover the emission detected by the SMA with a beam size of 3.1" x 2.4", a largest angular scale of 3" is needed.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_ANGULAR_RESOLUTION</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
        <prj:TechnicalJustification>
            <prj:justificationText>This is a polarization proposal, aimed at detecting polarized dust emission at 1.3 mm with an angular resolution of 0.5". Within the targeted area, our existing SMA observations have detected polarized emission at 0.88 mm with a beam size of 3.1" x 2.4", and the flux level is above 5 mJy/beam (the polarization degree is about 1%). We expect a similar polarization degree at 1.3 mm. Assuming that the polarized emission has a smooth distribution within the SMA beam and adopting a typical dust opacity index of 1.5, we could obtain an expected flux level of &gt;0.043 mJy/beam for the polarized emission observed with the ALMA, which is calculated from 5*(0.5^2/3.1/2.4)*(0.88/1.3)^3.5 = 0.043. So we request an RMS of 0.013 mJy/beam for detection with signal-to-noise ratios (S/N) above 3.</prj:justificationText>
            <prj:justificationKey>ED_SENSITIVITY</prj:justificationKey>
        </prj:TechnicalJustification>
